<reference id="boolean" xml:lang="en-us">
<title><xmlelement>boolean</xmlelement></title>
<shortdesc id="1.1">The <xmlelement>boolean</xmlelement> element was deprecated in DITA version 1.1.
        It was originally intended to express one of two opposite values, such as yes / no or on /
        off.
        <!--
If you need more than two values (for example, "yes," "no" and "don't care")
use the <ph><xref href="state.dita"><<keyword>state</keyword>&gt;</xref></ph> element
instead. This element is primarily for specialization, where it can be used
to require a logical true or false designation in a particular part of the
document.
--></shortdesc>
<prolog><metadata>
<keywords><indexterm>boolean</indexterm><indexterm>specialization elements<indexterm>boolean</indexterm></indexterm></keywords>
</metadata></prolog>
<refbody>
<section id="section-1"><note>This element is deprecated. It is functionally equivalent to <codeph>&lt;state
                    value="yes|no"/&gt;</codeph>, which is recommended as its replacement in all
                cases.</note></section>
<section id="contains" conref="../../common/commonNavLibraryTable.dita#contentmodel-boolean/contains" otherprops="contains"></section>
<section id="inheritance" otherprops="inheritance"><title>Inheritance</title><p>-
topic/boolean </p></section>
<example id="example" otherprops="examples"><title>Example</title><codeblock>She said "&lt;boolean state="yes"/&gt;" when I asked her to marry me!</codeblock></example>
<section id="attributes"><title>Attributes</title>
            <p>The following attributes are available on this element: <xref
                    href="../attributes/universalAttributes.dita#univ-atts"/>, <xref
                    href="../attributes/commonAttributes.dita#common-atts/outputclass"/>, and the
                attribute defined below.</p>
            <dl>
                <dlentry>
                    <dt><xmlatt>state</xmlatt>
                        <ph
                            conref="../../common/conref-attribute.dita#conref-attribute/required-attr"
                        /></dt>
                    <dd>The state of the <xmlelement>boolean</xmlelement> element. Allowable values
                        are "yes", "no", and "-dita-use-conref-target".</dd>
                </dlentry>
            </dl>
</section>
</refbody>
</reference>
